1. cs.DB (Database): The paper focuses on predicting query execution time, which is a fundamental issue in database management. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper uses a cost model to represent the query execution time as a function of selectivities and system performance constants, which involves machine learning techniques. 
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper deals with optimizing query plans and predicting execution time, which involves data structures and algorithms. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper uses random variables to infer the distribution of likely prediction errors, which involves machine learning techniques. 
5. cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper proposes a technique to provide uncertainty information along with query execution time predictions, which is relevant to software engineering.
